 HOPO at the wall similar to the CO\naccumulation during the quenching of premixed flames without flame retardant\naddition. The study shows how the structure of a partially premixed flame is\ninfluenced by a wall that releases either additional fuel or a mixture of fuel\nand flame retardant. The insights gained from the canonical configuration can\nlead to a better understanding of the combined effects of flame retardants and\nheat losses in near-wall flames.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Dec 2022 16:38:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-08"}
